Package fr.Infuseting.map

Class Place

java.lang.Object
fr.Infuseting.map.Place
public class Place extends Object
Represents a Place in a World. A World can have multiple Places but a Place can only have one World.
Author:
Mattheo

  • Constructor Details

    • Place

      public Place(int id, String name, Monster monster, String description, boolean end, boolean start, boolean defeat)
      Creates a Place with the specified parameters.
      Parameters:
      id - the identification number of the Place.
      name - the name of the Place.
      monster - The monster that is present in the Place. (Can be null)
      description - The description of the Place.
      end - The Place where the player needs to be in order to win.
      start - the Place where the player begins the game.
      defeat - a Place where the player dies and loses (GAME OVER !!).
